values:
Well, Malcolm and me are completely over. Getting over him wasn't as hard as I had thought, thanks to my friends. We're still friends and that makes me sooooooooo happy. Too much has happened in February; get over Malcolm, I turned 15, Tiffany and Ian broke up, Mallory and Anthony are back together, and I have a boyfriend. Nope, not Malcolm, but my best-friend Chris from 1st grade. "Awww!' *rolls eyes* I hear that all the time.
Softball starts on the 13th and I really need to step it up. I'm not getting my glove down on the ground like I should and it's pissing me off like no other! Grrr!!! Other than that, my batting is pretty decent. 

Babysitting is awesome! The two boys I 'sit are so adorable and I'm learning how to deal with their attitudes. For my birthday, Feb 22nd, I got a gift certificate, $40, and a cake!!! I never wanna give up this job! Also, mom's buying me a piccolo and got me a flute/piccolo case!

Theatre is dramatic as ever. We did okay at Regionals but went TEN SECONDS over our time limit... (Yet, we got home 10 minutes before Sadie's started. Dad did take me out and bought me my dress and shoes; Malcolm was my date. I do believe we all had fun.) Denise bruised her hand while packing up our set after we performed. OW!!! Most of us crashed in our homeroom after everything. Beauty and the Beast is very choppy but there's 2.5 months to perfect it. 

My birthday could've been better but it was fine! Mom gave me the case, friends were their usual selves, day was normal, and then I babysat that night. Mom and I went out to dinner once I got home then I had homework. Most of my theatre friends went all in and bought me Rent, which I've watched 6 times. =D Chris also asked me to be his girlfriend that Saturday but I told him to ask me on my b-day. (I really had to think it over becuase I'm so busy, a flirt, and been single for 9 months!) I said yes and we've been together for a week.

Drama is all around us. How we deal with it is our own dramatic episode.
Annie, the PoEtIc :D:D
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/17715.html

Heh, well, that last entry... Pay no attention. That was over by the time it started. I don't remember what I said but Greg and I barely talk to each other anymore, heh. So much has happened... I like another techie... Senior... Malcolm. *nods* He doesn't have a hidden girlfriend like Greg did so I did make an improvement. *smiles* I have liked hime for about a month and a half and he likes me too. Grrr!!! We can't have a relationship or date because he's going to college and he would feel like he's taking advantage of me. Oh, the age thing too. Can't forget the age... Malcolm and i have had talks about why we can't really be intimate and over affectionate. There was a time when we were affectionate; holding hands, holding each other, and small stuff like that. This past Saturday we had another talk on why we should go back to being friends. Malcolm, ever so often, does or says things that make me thing of the past and I'm upset for a while, I get over it, everythings good. Well, he doesn't want to hurt me so we're back to being just friends. That hurts me more, knowing that we can't be how we were last week! *shrug* Whatever makes departure less painful...

December went by fast; I visited my cousin Austin down at UofM, he sings opera, had first HS concert, Christmas, eat, drink, and be merry. My mom and I invited Malcolm to the hockey game on New Years; I drank that night and almost spilled my feelings to him. Then in January; became affectionate with Malcolm, tried out for Symphony band (made it), almost killed my knee, mid-terms and babysitting. (I've been babysitting for a while.)

Today Tiffany, Ian's girlfriend/fellow techie, and I got our hair done. It was just a major cut and highlights, for her. Mom won't let me color my hair again.

Theatre is, dramatic. More than likely we are going to Regional competition so everyone can kiss the Sadie Hawkin's dance au revior. (I asked Malcolm :D) Two of our actors won Superior awards at District's this past weekend. Our spring musical is "Beauty and the Beast." This will be the show that I am Assistant Stage Manager with Malcolm. He's not going to be here for the next 3 years, I will, and someone will need to be Stage Manager. Drama, softball, babysitting and homework make up my life.

All for now!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/17492.html

Whoa buddy! Say la vie to Andrew... Hello to the Techie boys. HA!

Marching band was a blast but I still miss it. Now for concert I'm playing flute and piccolo. It took a while for Mr. Jones to give me the piccolo. I have it, I love it, and I can play it. No body else in the concert band really wants to play it or they just can't. Yeah, my ego is talking... a bit. hehe

Yeah, Andrew made me mad that night so I've been avoiding him. I don't like him anymore and I don't know why I did in the first place. Damn players! Quit looking at me! Lately we've been talking online but very scarcely. Last night he told me to call him but 1) It was 10 at night 2) Mom wouldn't let me 3) I didn't want to 4) Louie needed me 5) I like someone else.

The play, The Jungle Book, went really well. Denise, Greg (a senior), and me flipped these curtains for night and day. After our last flip we'd go backstage and just chill. On Tuesday Greg and Malcolm left Denise, Cait and me at school so we decided to start walking. They seemed not to believe us be we walked all the way to Calkins Road.

 Greg's nickname is Flirt and that's pretty much what he is. I flirted back and feelings grew. *hides* Not again... I would just sit on his lap and we'd talk and kind of flirt. Heckwe flirted. Denise and Cait told me that Wednesday that he had a girlfriend, yeah it hurt but I wanted to see if he'd tell me. Like a stereotypical male, he didn't. I kind of busted him on it Friday. Greg wanted a back massage so I gave him one and Malcolm made a comment about a girlfriend. *eyes change color* Whoa buddy! "You never told me you had a girlfriend" "It's a long story. I'll tell you later." Gah! We then had to leave for the choir room and I really didn't want to be near him. He grabbed my wrist, making me face him. I just glared as he said something about having a girlfriend and not doing this. In the choirroom we did the hand squeeze and he kept holding my hand like we used to. *glare* I was crushed. Back on stage, Greg tells me that he didn't feel the same for his girlfriend and that he was going to break up with her this weekend. Uncertain, I tried to smile and grabbed his hand. Show went on, we hung out backstage, I told Denise what was happening. She tried to keep me from crying. Greg and I hung out until the cast party. I couldn't really eat because of my nerves. We talked that night online and he said that things changed AGAIN. X_X Him and his girlfriend of almost a year are still together. Don't flirt if you have a serious relationship, gosh. Feelings get hurt! We reconciled and we're friends now. My feelings for Greg are still how they were, several tears later. The cast party Saturday night was at his house but my mom picked Marie and me up before 11. >_> Greg and I hugged before we left and I asked him what changed over night. He doesn't know how, what he wants, etc. Love is fickle!

Besides that, life is good. All my grades are up in the A, B range. I gave my second speech for Mrs DiGiacomo that I literally pulled out of my tukkus. I went Up North for Thanksgiving. (Bacardi with Pepsi and Smirnoff green apple is really good.) i need to study some more so peace out!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/17338.html

Heyo!

Great Lakes Invitational went well. 2nd place out of 2 schools XD. We improved to 54.95 which is a 55. I didn't talk to anyone else at that festival.But it wasn't as cold as it normally was when we performed. I'll miss it but my schedule is a lot lighter, now I only work at the elementary and private flute lessons where I had practices.

Andrew and I have became good friends. We talk online and on the phone so it's all good. He's very cute like I said in my last post but he's cute when I get to hear his voice all the time. Then again, he's your typical guy which can be agitating. But right now he's make me very mad. :D *controls temper...deep breath* Next topic...

I got the job at Subway but I don't know when I'm working again. Hopefully soon because I need the money for lessons and these Converses I want. Halloween was fun. Ziggy had a party, we went to a haunted house, wanted to TP Shawn's house but didn't, trick-or-treated with some of my younger friends.

I need to head of so peace out!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/17026.html

*sigh* Can I please move to Clarkston, Novi, or Taylor Truman? Why, you may ask.... BECAUSE THEY KICK @$$ and are discipled. Also, I made friends with people frome Clarkston and Truman. Last weekend we made a 7 point improvement, last place, and last night *shudders* We dropped 3 points which wouldn't have helped. Truman still beat us by 6 points. But at Festival last night, I had a little girl kick dirt at me after I had a disagreement with some friends. I wanted to cry so bad and I almost fell in the 3rd movement. Stupid moves that we flutes have to march almost 4-5 instead. The astro-turf at Plymouth-Canton was slippery; I almost pulled a hamstring. Anyway, after I watched some other band, I got in line for something warm to eat. This really cute guy from Taylor striked up a conversation and we hanged out for a while. His name is Andrew XD and plays trumpet. He was soo sweet! I was freezing cold even though I had so much clothes on and he offered me to wear his band jacket. I said no (damnit) and just walked around with him and his friends. Finally, I found Denise and we jsut goofed around. Awards: 9th place, embarrassed by the band, teared up, froze. Going to the bus, I seen Andrew again and he put his arm around me and we exchanged email addresses and he gave me a hug! Holy fruit basket! I miss him but we compete against him and it's kind of awkward... Oh well!

I have a job interview tomorrow at Subway in the mall after school. I put in my application finally and talked to the manager. I'm extremely nervous about tomorrow; not sure what to say but do know what to wear. Dad is going to help pay for Drivers Training next month and Im going over there the weekend after Halloween. And one more festival this weekend. I heard that this own is the hardest besides this weekend. (GL Invitational.)

I'm over tired so peace out!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC

PS...RANDOMNESS!
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/16884.html

Hmm... Hey everyone!

Devin and I went put-putting a couple weekends ago, That was fun and embarrassing because I suck at golf. Then he wouldn't talk to me until this week. It's just been really weird. But things seem to finally be setting down around here. School is becoming more managable, especially Accel. English. This project we got on Monday just was so over-wehlming until I found a book that I could understand and understood the whole project. The lowest grade I have in all my classes is a B. :D Sooo happy about that. Academically, things are going just dandiful.

HoMeCoMiNg! That was soo much fun! No, excellent-awesome-totally-freakin-nifty! Well, Devin didn't go with me because he already had a date. My mom said to invite Derrick, my friend from Kindergarten to come with me. He did and it was absolutely superbed. Him, Marie and me all went together. Marie looked simply divine, Derrick was quite handsome and I was quite a charmer myself. (It was really hilarious to watch Debbie put Derricks buotineer on.) With our hair done, nails perfected (not mine :P), and sucking in our gut, Marie and me were angels for the night. We went to Applebee's and seen some otehr kids from school. At the dance, Haley, Charlie, Nicole, Andrew, Sam, Devin, Cait, Denise, and everyone else was there. Of course, Denise and I danced like how we planned; freakishly hot! I taught Derrick how to dance and slow dance, got Marie and Cait out of their shell and just had a hella good time! Some of us even danced with Wesley, one of the theatre guys. (He's gay so it's all good.)

Theatre: I am going to become a thespian. Tomorrow afternoon we have a work day noon-4 to work on the set for "The Jungle Book". I'm quite estacting for that (can't you tell by my ethusiasm...) It's something to keep my friends and myself busy and together.

Tomorrow is Melissa's birthday party, our Cheeze Head party/sleep-over. My WHOLE week is already planned out and I hate it. (Did I mention that I don't have time for a life?)

Monday: theatre meetings, homework Tuesday: Homework, band practice Wednesday: Babysitting, homework Thursday: Work, band practice, homework Friday: Football games Saturday: Festivals, homework Sunday: Homework

I must go so peace out!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/16612.html

This week is awesome! So far, I have A's and B's in my classes. This past weekend I had a 4 page pursasive essay for english to do. I just typed that today and I'm not sure when it's due. lol  I love High School!

Devin, Cait and me all walk to 3 hour together but Devin and I are talking more... Hehe...I asked him to Homecoming but he hasn't told me his responce yet. Grr...I really hope he gets online soon or calls me when I get offline. I'm just really hyped up.

My bus was packed to 3 in a seat but now our bus is splited into 2 busses. Which means, Andrew doesn't ride my bus, yay!, but Will doesn't, aww. That half sucks, half rocks because now I actually have a spot to sit.

I can't think of anything else so peace out!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/16289.html

Today was awesome! Well, most of it was. lol This morning I went to Taras that way I wouldn't have to stand out in the cold but her brother took us to school which was awesome. I got up with Cait and Kassie before homeroom. Jessi Thoma is in there that I know form softball so that was cool. We just watched a boring powerpoint presentation on the hand book then 1st hour came. I went into the wrong first hour! lol I went a door down when I was supposed to be 2 doors down. There's not a whole lot of Freshmen but Upperclassman that are trying to get their last few credits before graduating. But they didn't have a computer for me so I just pulled up a seat near Tiffany Vaughn (Cait gave me a death glare when I told her.) She was the only person I really knew in the class. Syllabus's and the talk, blah blah blah. On the way to 2nd hour, Dayna and I were supposed to meet up by the stairway because we're upstairs but I couldn't find her so I headed to Geometry. Once I got in there, I seen Dayna...AND CAIT! Major freakin' w00tness! Cait and Dayna and me are all in the same Geometry class...Fun year ahead hehe. And there's this really hot guy named Devin Murphy that sits next to me and he kept looking at me so I introduced myself and we got talking... He is REALLY cute! And he's on the swim team. ;) Finally, a sexy guy in a speedo! lol Unfortuanitly, Brooke Silva and Megan McCartney are both in my class. I don't like them at all ever since 7th grade on the bus. Ms. Sokol just talked and we did an introduction thingy. Stuff like that. From their I went to Phys Ed were the Varsity softball coach is my teacher. How sweet is that?! She just told us the main stuff about her class and that we have softball tomorrow!! Double Sweet! I asked her when weight lifting begins and it doens't start till around the winter...Gr! Just means that I have to do my own work out until then. :( From Gym I went to lunch and Dayna and I walked around for a bit, stalked Chase, then ate. Come to find out, Chase hangs out with the gothic people...Weeiirrdd. We finally went and got some bosco sticks for lunch. We got to eat one then the bell rang. I feel really bad because it's my fault for running around the school and stalking Chase. Band was next and was for a couple hour. Mr Jones just talked about festivals, etc. Accelerated English I is my 5th hour and that seems hard...Well, more-so challeneging so bring it on Mrs. DiGiacomo! Grrr!!! lol I'm really hyped up for tomorrow! We got our syllabus and she talked and talked and talked. We have a quiz tomorrow on one of our books. On the way to sixth hour I passed Chase and he had his book like he was going to hit me but I just punched him on his shoulder. haha He was like, "Oww!" and started laughing. I got into Biology and that seems like fun. We had to do a 15 question thingy already. Thankfully we don't get our books for another 2 weeks because Mrs Lawrence is trying to save our backs...Literally.

On the way to homeroom today, I passed Shawn and one of his friends. They called my name and I just turned my head and glared... I didn't want to be late on the first day! I feel really sorry for Marie. She sits behind him in 5th hour. Besides Devin looking good, there was this one guy in the hall I seen that resembled Louie... Just cockier and arrogant. Pssh that! I need to head off... I won't get picked up until 6:45 which means I can sleep in until 5:30 at least. Bye!!!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC fReShMaN

PS. Andrew aka Flubber rides my bus and Will gave me a kiss on my forehead at band practice lol
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/16049.html

Yesterday my mom and I didn't really do anything but go to Tom and Teresa's house for dinner. Nothing too exciting there but the German Shepard puppies. They are soo cute...and huge!

But because last night was my last night to stay up, I stayed up till 2:30 and wokeup around 10. Mom and I only went to Meijers and did a dry-run for her bus. Then we just came home and chilled. I made dinner, steak and baked potato, took a look bubble bath with candles... It was soo relaxing. Tomorrow I have school so I plucked my eye brows, shaved my legs, did my nails, and that kind of stuff. My back pack is all ready to go! Well, I have to get up around 5-5:30 so peace!

Annie, the PyScHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/15623.html

Hey. I'm exhausted once again. My mom and I just went shopping pretty much all day. At Pets Supplies Plus I got Lily a pimpin pink colar lol. (She didn't like it at first but now she does.) Then we went to Wal*Mart and Mom bought me these one pair of flats that were similar to the ones at Hot Topic. They go quite well with my skirt for the first day. Um, we then went to Confers for meat, then headed to Petsmart where my day got interesting.

We needed a algea eater for our fish tank so we got one and we were walking down the aisle and I seen Sage, Shawn's half-bro and in mid step, I turned around and took off to the back of the story, then to the restrooms. I must say, I looked pretty hot in tight jeans, white tank with my batman hoodie and eye liner. Mom and I met up in the kitten adoption area and Shawn's dad taps on the glass behind me so I just turned around and waved. Then they had to come in and look at the kittens. Being in the same small space with Shawn wasn't very comforting. He got his hair cut short in the back with long bangs...similar to mine. XP I'm tempted to cut them off now. Thankfully, that was the last I seen of him until Tuesday. Knowing my luck, I'll have a class with him and probably gym/swimming....NOOO!!! *screams while falling into darkness* Pour quoi?! POUR QUOI?! Another interesting year with not only Shawn, but also Andrew....Grrr....Why?! WHY?!

Well, we came back home, ate, talked to Marie and just been chilling online. I swear Louie and Bruce will become a couple sooner or later.  No Homecoming date yet.

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/15418.html

Yo, I'm just whipped although I just helped Mr. Maynard today. He didn't need me till 9 so I just layed on the couch once I got outta the shower. We finished putting his classroom in order and went to Office Depot to pick up some file thingies. While he was in the check out line, I went and checked out some digital cameras; There's a couple I liked. I have been thinking about getting one. Once we left, he took me to Burger King and I got lunch. We first went to McDonalds and he turned the wrong way and almost hit comeone head on then almost took a wrong turn but, obviously, I'm still alive. I started laughing and Derek was like, "Don't be lauging at me," and was poking me. It's fun to joke around with him. We then went back to the school and I was writing the student names in ABC order and I put this kid's name after the S's and it was an O. Major blonde moment of the day.

He took me home, I went over to Amandas because she called. She had my money from her sister for babysitting Tuesday. I just stayed over there because I didn't feel like sitting home alone and bored. Once I did come home, I just layed down and watch tv, play my guitar a bit.

For once Mom and I went out to dinner. We went to Red Lobster and there was this little boy that sat behind her and was making too much noise. I was thinking, "Happy Birthday you little brat now shut up and let me eat my dinner in silence!" Go figure, when we got our bill, they left. *scowls* I wasn't too happy. Then we came home and I went over to Mallory's to see if she was home, wasn't, and just rode around then back home, got online to the point where I am now. I don't think I'm going to be online fo rmuch long because I am exhausted again!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/15344.html

I'm barely awake but tonight was awesome!!! The energy, joking around, music, everything went right. We even crushed SC 49-17! Talk about awesome. And Ahmad Rashad made this almost dash to the end zone. Some of my friends and I made up a parody to My Chemical Romance to My Bi-sexual Romance with "I'm not Straight (Yet)". We were so hyped up before going out ther. But for pre-game, while marching out to the field, I miss my spot but marched back and made it look good. lol My mom just made it for half time. I saw her and had a big smile. Although Nate said that he couldn't come to the game, he did make it and that was cool. Marie was also there. Her dad dropped her off, I guess, and we took her home.

Bowling earlier was good. Nancee decided to take Marie for some strange reason so Denise picked up Anna, Me, then Nate. Charles and Stacia couldn't go but we still had fun. Nate and I wore the same color of shirt but, yeah, his was a guys and mine was a chicks... Obviously. It was funny though. I changed my name to Gerard and was wearing Nate's "lucky hat" and got 4 strikes in a row. That was awesome. Anna was talking to Martini on the phone and I think he asked her what happened cause I heard her say, "Annie just got 4 strikes in a row."  I was thinking, "Yeah! What now Flubber?!" I talked to him for like 10 seconds and at first he didn't realize that it was me. lol Before we started bowling, Anna was playing with a quater and it went half way down a gutter and me being me, I went after it and almost fell on the lane. The guy at the counter seemed pissed but one of the other guys just laughed at my stupidity. Those lanes are slippery-er than freshy sharpened skates on smooth ice.

Once I got home I seen that Mr Maynard called and he wants me to help him out tomorrow so peace out!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/14866.html

We kept working on the pre-game show last night and made some improvement. Not enough to where I'm jumping for joy about that. The Half Time show is what I'm psyched about! And Nate, Marie, Denise, Anna and maybe Charles and Stacia and me are going bowling tomorrow. Denise forgot to call Aaron so if Stacia and Charles don't go, it'll be the 5 of us. Nate is starting to make it more obvious that he likes me. I told him that I got my hair cut tonight becuase I forgot to tell him a long time ago and he said, "I'm sure it stills looks good." Then that I didn't take a shower today, "You can't stink. Chicks can't, I'm sure you smell fine." Kinda creepy but the best attention since Louie... Which I think Louie and Bruce might end up hooking up in some kind of relationship. It's like my own version of  Laguna Beach because of all this other drama that's already happening before school with relationships, crushes, etc. No date yet for Homecoming.

Tomorrow night is my FIRST marching show! Oh my gosh am I ever hyper and excited for it!!! Weeee! If it's too hot, we're just going to wear our shirts from camp but if someone doesn't wear the right one, we ALL have to wear our windbreakers. XP I will so kill that person if it's hot tomorrow night. But what I think is really hilarious is that for this one cerimonial thingy, we're playing "The Final Countdown". That's great, eh? lol

Today I spent my day in my pajamas, making brownies, and looking for scholarships online. I already sent out two that I did online. The others are a poem and some essays. One that should be really easy is "How Does Playing a Musical Intrument Make You a Better Student?" That one and this one about science theories which I love because anything is possible. Well, I got to get to bed!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/14697.html

Well, Denise couldn't come over because her mother decided at the very last moment that she had to stay home and help fix the toliet. That must've sucked. I got to talk to her for a few minutes while she was doing that. I got off the phone with her then 30-45 minutes later, Marie calls me back and I absent mindedly asked her to spend the night. She did and we had our normal good laughs.

We went to bed about 1 o'clock but kept talking and talking and talking and, yeah, talking some more. Marie and I talked till 2 and woke up at a little bit after 10 to go for a walk. That was very up-lifting, if you will.We walked to the subdivision where my old babysitter lives (which is about a mile). Around 11:30 we got back and we ordered pizza because my mom had to get her bus fixed for tomorrow. Within 30 minutes, we both took our showers and got dressed. That should be in the Ginus Book of World Records. lol Our pizza was gooood. We saved some for my mom because we're just nice like that. :D Yeah, right.

Once she got home, Marie and I got online for an hour and looked at dresses seeing who has more of an expensive taste. We're about even. Her step-mom picked her up after 3 then my mom had to go back and completely re-arrange her pick up times and go to the bus garage. I went with her thinking I could help her with the times and all that. She then had to go undo what she did this morning. Mom started to get really teary eyed because this has been really stressful on her. Her one friend ended up taking me home where I just lounged around and munched until she got back home around 6:30. I continued to lounged, eat, watch TV, and play in the rain.

Tomorrow I have to babysit but thankfully I don't have to wake up till 7:45-8:00 and not get there till 8:30-ish. It will be just Robert which mean I'm defiantely bringing my books and my walking shoes. Ethan has school tomorrow and won't get home till his mom does. (3:30) I pray that it will be an easy day for me because I also have band tomorrow and it's our last practice before our first show.

I'm so hyped for our first home game/show! Oh my gosh! I can't explain how happy and excited I am for it! Mr Jones really needs us to work on our pre-game show and our new drill charts. Still, I am confused on where to go and how big of steps I am to take. I stand between the 30 and 35 and go to the inside of the 20. I think it's supposed to be 16 steps or something. Not only am I to worry about that, but if I'm in line with everyone else and playing my music. *sigh* It should be fine. I'm just a rookie, not a 3 year veteran.

Well, all for now!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/14406.html

I really felt bad for my dad because he wasn't feeling well while we were shopping. I got things from stores I normally wouldn't buy from. Charlotte Russe, Forever 21, 5-7-9 but Hot Topic is a must!

Charlotte Russe: Two pairs of comfy pants with a apricot colored half shirt that had a white shirt underneath.

5-7-9: A pair of Paris Blues jeans. I was going to get a tan pair but they both were $24 and I wanted money for H.T.

Forever 21: A pair of jeans that are tight on my booty but a bit baggy on my legs. I also got a green zip-up hoodie that says Intense. And pink lip gloss that smells like Trix cereal. 

Hot Topic!: A blue Alice in Wonderland tee with a Batman hoodie that's really thin. And a realyl cute pair of dangly star cluster earrings.

We were in Hot Topic for 20 minutes and my dad started to get a fever so I had to grab whatever I wanted and go to the counter. I really wish he was feeling better so we could've stayed. Dad said that he would take me again when he was feeling better to "go finish." Hehe! More clothes, the better! I got to go eat and Denise will be over later so peace!

Annie, the PsYcHoTiC
http://shining17star.livejournal.com/14330.html

I woke up a little before noon because my mom was talking to me. (She had some errands to go do.) Which means I'm going to be late to go to softball with my friends! Oh well...It only starts at 1! lol Later today, my neighbor is having a cook out and is cooking A LOT of food! He is the bestestestest cook that I know. We got BBQ ribs, different kinds of salads, sweet potatoes, corn, and all that good stuff. I can't wait till later tonight!

This time tomorrow, I should be with my dad shopping. I'm overwhelmed because I know what I want but I don't think he plans on spending that much. Maybe I could get assceories for my dresses! And those cute shoes at Hot Topic, and adorable jeans at 5-7-9...Ahh! It's all too much! I'll take it all! lol But at least I get to spend time with my dad more than when I was younger.

Well, that's pretty much it for the afternoon. Peace out!
